text:
The marketing department as a whole has undergone quite a substantial overhaul and upgrade.  There's a tonne of initiatives in the pipe and we, have developed better tools for analysing the results of targeted campaigns etc.  I think you'll see a solid increase in marketing overall towards the end of the year.

Also I will point out that while we who are still here, focus on crypto every day, the vast majority of the world has still tuned out.  I think this chart really shows just how much retail has tuned out. I firmly believe that all the non-stop building and maturation of the company has us in a great spot to capture the market when it returns.  Not that we are sitting on our hands waiting for that moment, but I think it's important to keep that in perspective.

Credit to Benjamin Cowen and his website

If what theyâ€™re saying on the French group about YA making the decision to keep YLD separate from H1 then I think itâ€™s the right decision and it shows theyâ€™ve listened to community feedback 

Haven is likely to be much more interesting for non-retail players (eg institutions) than it is for the typical retail crowd 

Of course thereâ€™s nothing to stop you from buying it directly but now youâ€™d have the choice of how/where to allocate your funds 

So all in all Iâ€™d say thatâ€™s a v positive decision if it turns out to be true 

That still leaves open the question of how to optimise the tokenomics of YLD going forward but thatâ€™s a separate matter which everyone here has their own opinion on

messages.text: In the future do you think Yield could offer the option of not re-investing interest? For example now if you lock your USDT for year the principal and interest is tied up for a year or more. But for YLD we can lock a certain number of tokens and the interest is basically paid into our unlocked wallet. If we could choose to not have the interest re-invested then it would be a good way to invest and plan for the daily needs. For example you could lock 100 K worth of USDT and then have about USD 1000 per month to spend without touching the locked USDT. It would be even better if YLD had a credit card then you could use the monthly interest to pay off the credit card balances.

messages.text:
Still 20 000 YLD will be needed to stay/become Diamond. Meaning that every new user who will join us, potentially might want to become new Diamond user. Is is worth it? Well, itâ€™s up to everybody to decide by themselves.

Perks for Diamond users:

- MUCH higher rates for all cryptocurrencies
- access to even higher rates thanks to Earn+ 365
- 3 free crypto withdrawals
- 1 free fiat withdrawal
- access to VIP chat on Discord
- occasional educational materials send via e-mail

PLUS now two nice additions coming:
- owning significant number of tokens with inflation basically coming to an end
- staking YLD will earn you H1 and let you that way to participate in Haven1 project if you wish to continue staking

Is list of perks for YLD holders depleted? Definitely not, we will do our best to add more utility in the future. However, most importantly, success of Haven1 will be success of Yield App and vice versa as two separate teams will be definitely promoting each other directly and indirectly. And itâ€™s not like Yield App team members left one team and joined Haven1. Both teams will keep growing like in the past 12 months (at least 50% more team members in case of Yield App). ðŸ’ª

messages.text: It's really nice that Yield app listened to their community. Unfortunately, I didn't and still don't agree with the majority of the community. I rather sell the excess YLD and buy H1 tokens with it.

text:
: initially, if I understood correctly,  there was supposed to be a swap from YLD tokens to haven tokens effective at the launch of Haven1, the haven1 tokens were taken from the initially announced supply of Haven1 and they could be used in the same way as YLD for staking rewards and tiers in the app and additionally participate in the Haven1 ecosystem.

Under the new announced conditions, Yld holders will keep the Yld tokens, the yld staked will be paid a yield in locked Haven1 tokens that are blocked for 5 years.

I really fail to see the advantages for YLD holders so far.

First version you make a swap you get the Haven1 immediately, usable for ecosystem rewards and keep the perks in the app provided that you stake them.

Second version, you keep the YLD, (that has no additional utility) and you get locked Haven1 as interest on it (locked for 5 y).

According to me, Yld holders are given nothing of immediate value or usability.

I understand that we will not be diluted in YLD, but we actually don't get any immediately usable H1.

Looking forward for the AMA

messages.text:
The physical aspect of the card is the easiest part. 
Just look at what's happening with fiat rails all over the world. A card is essentially a fiat rail in your pocket. 
We don't disagree that a card would be nice, it's just not the highest priority for us to develop at this time.  I too hope we will have the best crypto card, just like we have the best fiat rails, but a lot has changed since 2021.  Vast majority of the card programs out there fell short of their goals.  Like all things at Yield App, we prefer to stick to the conservative, bulletproof approach that has served us well to date.

messages.text:
I don't foresee a time where we would want to charge a fee to deposit. Especially for Diamond Tier users.
We just have to give ourselves the option to make adjustments. For example, if there was a massive flood of people using our fiat rails just to on and offramp, without actually using the platform to earn, it would become an admin burden for no benefit. So like many things, I would just encourage you to consider the business from a common sense perspective, we will give you free fiat rails so long as it's viable to do so.  It's not like we secretly, have some date in mind when we will slap a massive fee.

If a time comes where we need to look to adjust, we'll asset it then and hopefully make a decision that ensures we are covered and at the same time looks after clients like you and your friends.
